723572f-a.title: Manhattan: Trinity Place - Rector Street
723572f-a.text:
56-66, 68, and 72-76 (left to right) Trinity Place, at, adjoining and
north of the N.N. corner of Rector Street, shoving the 26-story Electric
Bond and Share Co. Building (No. 56-66), the 6-story Horn and Hardart
Building (No. 68), and the 24-story Trinity Court Building as seen across
the Rector Street station of the Sixth Ave. Elevated Line. Also shown
(foreground) is a portion of Trintty Church, and grave yard extending
west from Broadway to Trinity Place. On the extreme left is Rector Street
west from Broadway (not seen) to and including West Street, with Pier 8
and the Hfudson River partially visible. This view was taken from the
New York Stock Exchange Building, at the S.W. corner of Broad and Wall
Streefs.
August 7, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
723572f-a.folder: Trinity Place & Rector Street, Manhattan, NY

723571f-b.title: Manhattan: Trinity Place - Rector Street
723571f-b.text:
(1)
Trinity Place, south from and including Rector Street, showing
(richt foreground) a portion of the 23-story building No. 2 Rector Street
at the N.W. corner; the rear of Trinity Church (left foreground), and a
portion of the 21-story Empire Building at the S.E. corner of Rector
Street. Also shown (centre background) is the 32-story Whitehall Building
at the N.W. corner of West Street and Battery Place, and the Statue of
Liberty (Bedloe's Island) faintly discernible. Note also a portion of
the Sixth Ave. Elevated line.
August 20, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
Trinity Tlace and Broadway,showing Trinity Church nand Church Yerd.
